javaslang.collection

Interface RoseTree<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of a Node's value.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Tree<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RoseTree.NonNil<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RoseTree.AbstractRoseTree, RoseTree.Branch, RoseTree.Leaf, RoseTree.Nil

    public interface RoseTree<T>
extends Tree<T>
    A rose tree implementation, i.e. a tree with an arbitrary number of children, where each node keeps a value.

    See Rose tree (wikipedia).

    Since:
    1.1.0

static <T> RoseTree.NonNil<T> of(T value,
                                              RoseTree.NonNil<T>... children)
        Creates either a rose tree branch or a leaf, depending on the child count. By definition, a node with no children is a leaf.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The value type
        Parameters:
        value - The value of the node.
        children - The tree node's non-empty children, i.e. leafs and branches.
